programme.desc: Life is all about Give and Take. At some point, we all have to choose a side. The sad thing is it may be friends over family. Black Diamond is a film about a Diamond that was born a Gem but raised a Savage.

programme.title: The Lying Truth #Plex

programme.title: Captured

programme.desc: The Legend of Black Annie is a film loosely based on an urban legend. It starts in the late 1960s and ends in 2012. When a group of mischievous boys accidentally kill a young girl, her mother, who is versed in the art of voodoo, enacts revenge upon them a

programme.desc: This is a story about Vampires and the struggle for rulership amongst the elders and elites. Humanity is at stake and if the wrong House is nominated for rulership it could be doom for the living.

programme.title: Not Another Zombie Movie

programme.desc: Sisters Tracy and Lena are sleeping with each others husbands, Von and Alex. The punishment is worse than the crime when all become entangled in more than just lies and deception, but also murder.

programme.title: Lies We Tell But The Secrets We Keep Sweet Revenge
programme.desc: Bri is on life support fighting for her life, while Roni is trying to find Tank, to seek revenge, and take matters into her own hands.

programme.title: Cake
programme.desc: Young pastry chef, Ronnie, dreams of opening her own bakery, but friends, family, and her love life have plans of their own.

programme.title: Maverick Movies
programme.desc: For years Tiffany has been wanting to leave her relationship, but she is terrified on how her abusive boyfriend Mike will react. Money and stress seem to be the backbone for Mike behaving so abusively towards her. With one year left in school, Tiffany con

programme.title: Invisible Lies
programme.desc: A Black lawyer must come to grip with his prejudices after falling in love with a White woman while simultaneously defending a Black teenager who has been wrongfully accused of drugging and raping his White girlfriend.

programme.title: You Look Familiar: Vernee Watson
programme.desc: Actress Vernee Watson has broken ground and paved the way for black actresses on television today: with a career spanning over 4 decades, 3 Emmy awards, and costars such as Will Smith and Denzel Washington. Learn her life story onscreen and off.

programme.title: Purgatory
programme.desc: Grieving widower, Bernard, is approached by a spiritual healer and a voodoo high priest with an enticing offer to reconnect with his late wife, Sophia, in the afterlife. In the process, Bernard faces spirits, demons, and life-altering secrets.

programme.title: Music & Murder
programme.desc: Not every rags to riches story arrives via a clean cut straight and narrow path. Sometimes long after the rags have been replaced with Versace, the stench from the counterfeit mindset lingers longer than a starlet would like.

programme.title: Music & Murder 2
programme.desc: After Chastity is found, the women of Venom studios must put life back together and keep the studios running. While they attempt to keep the business running smoothly, the women discover a new threat in the form of a potential friend. Now they have to fin

programme.title: True Colors
programme.desc: Trevor Winfield is a former street thief turned painter, who is now in a relationship with his girlfriend Sophia Clifford. After he finds himself in debt to a drug lord, he is faced with the ultimatum of staging a heist against his wealthy girlfriend to p

programme.title: Elvira's Movie Macabre: The Doomsday Machine
programme.desc: Elvira showcases the 1972 Sci-Fi Disaster film The Doomsday Machine which follows a group on a spaceship who witnessed the earth being destroyed.

programme.title: Elvira's Movie Macabre: They Came From Beyond Space
programme.desc: Elvira presents the 1967 Sci-Fi classic They Came Beyond Space.

programme.title: Elvira's Movie Macabre: The House That Screamed
programme.desc: Elvira showcases the 1969 Horror Thriller The House That Screamed. The story centers at a isolated school for girls where students keep dissapearing.

programme.title: Beast from Haunted Cave (Friday Fright)
programme.desc: A giant spider stalks a band of thieves in this schlocky thriller from Gene Corman Productions. The story follows gangster Alexander Ward and his crew as they enlist the help of a local ski-instructor in the heist of several gold bars. But when they use explosives to create a distraction, they disturb the lair of a massive spider! Monte Hellman, the man behind such cult favorites as Two-Lane Blacktop, made his directorial debut with Beast From Haunted Cave. Trivia note: This movie debuted on a double bill with The Wasp Woman.

programme.title: Teenagers from Outer Space (Friday Fright)
programme.desc: A teenager falls in love with a young alien. Together, they must stop the alien's race from destroying the human race.

programme.title: The Ape Man (Friday Fright)
programme.desc: This campy yet compelling horror classic stars none other than the legendary Bela Lugosi as Dr. James Brewster who embarks on an ill-fated endeavor to find an antidote after he turns himself into a hairy, stooped-over ape-man. When Dr. Brewster discovers that the key ingredient of the antidote is recently drawn human spinal fluid, he is abandoned by his assistant and must rely on the help of his captive gorilla to aid him in his search for an appropriate donor.

programme.title: White Zombie (Friday Fright)
programme.desc: Watch Bela Lugosi use his special zombie grip to make beautiful women submit to his every desire! In this low budget screamer, a couple honeymooning in Haiti run afoul of a diabolical voodoo master. They’re soon wishing they’d gone to Cancun! This Pre-­Code horror classic is considered to be the first feature length zombie movie, and features great atmospheric direction by Victor Halperin. The film’s unsung hero was set designer Ralph Berger, who exploited sets of previous Universal Studios films, including bits from Dracula, The Hunchback of Notre Dame, and Frankenstein. Whatever you do, DON’T LOOK INTO LUGOSI’S EYES!

programme.title: Castle of the Living Dead
programme.desc: A traveling theatre troupe are thrilled with their luck when they are invited to the castle of the mysterious but alluring Count Drago. But a chilling prediction from a strange old woman casts a shadow over the impending visit. Once at the castle, the party find a room full of stuffed birds waiting for them...or at least they seem to be. Count Drago has a terrible secret.

programme.title: Beyond Alantis
programme.desc: A band of adventurers invade a native island determined to grab a reported fortune in buried treasure. The islanders are just as determined to keep their sacred treasure. Complications ensue.

programme.title: Curse of Bigfoot (1975)
programme.desc: Beware - not of Bigfoot, but of this movie! A group of high school kids go exploring in a cave and stumble upon a mummy, but when they remove it, the nasty old thing comes to life and starts terrorizing their small California town! If this doesn't look exactly like a 1970s movie, that's because producer/director Dave Flocker shot most of it in 1958 as Teenagers Battle the Thing. Bigfoot enthusiasts might be appalled, but lovers of schlock might find this feature to be just what they need!

programme.title: Devil's Daughter
programme.desc: Sylvia Walton returns from Harlem to take over a Jamaican plantation from her vindictive half-sister, amid the growing sound of drums.

programme.title: Road to Bali
programme.desc: Bob Hope and Bing Crosby are two rascals trying to leave Melbourne to avoid impending wedding dates. They take jobs as divers and end up on an island, where each tries to win the affections of the exotic Princess Lala (Dorothy Lamour). Director Hal Walker (My Friend Irma, That's My Boy) keeps the fun coming in this one, with plenty of songs and gags. And if uncredited cameos by the likes of Jerry Lewis, Dean Martin, and Jane Russell aren't enough to entice you, this is the only Road To... movie made in color!

programme.title: Crimson Romance (1934)
programme.desc: Realistic air battles are the highlight of this Depression era treat. The topnotch cast includes Ben Lyon (Hell’s Angels, Night Nurse)and Erich Von Stroheim (Sunset Boulevard, Blind Husbands), all on-hand to tell the romantic tale of an American flying ace and his charming little fraulein.

programme.title: Guest in the House (1944)
programme.desc: Anne Baxter and Ralph Bellamy star in this drama about a conniving woman who turns a happy household against itself. The trouble starts when a sickly young woman is invited to stay with her fiance’s family at their country home to enjoy the fresh air and atmosphere. But why does the lady of the house feel that something evil has entered? The film is in the tradition of Alfred Hitchcock’s Shadow of a Doubt, and includes an Oscar nominated musical score by Werner Jannsen with cinematography by the highly revered Lee Garmes (Duel In The Sun, Jungle Book).

programme.title: Bells of San Angelo (1947)
programme.desc: Roy Rogers and Dale Evans team up in this tale of silver mines, kidnappings, and secret passages. Roy plays a border guard who has to rescue Dale from the clutches of underhanded miner Rex Gridley (John McGuire). How does he do it? With help from Trigger, of course! With a cast that inclues Andy Devine as Sheriff Cookie Bullfincer, director William Witney gives us an enjoyable drama from the golden era of Republic Pictures!

programme.title: Daniel Boone (1936)
programme.desc: In 1775, Daniel Boone (George O'Brien) leads thirty colonial families to Kentucky where they face the threats of Native American marauders led by rebel Simon Girty (John Carradine). That's just the beginning, for there are even more dangers and clashes ahead for Boone and his party. With a cast that includes Ralph Forbes, Heather Angel, and lovable child star Dickie Jones, director David Howard takes us through one of the most exciting periods in American history!

programme.title: Go For Broke (1951)
programme.desc: "Go for Broke" follows the exploits of the most decorated unit in US Army history - the 442nd Regiment - the first all-Nisei (Japanese-American) combat team in WWII. Van Johnson stars as a commanding officer who must overcome his own prejudices as he trains and leads his men through battles on the European Front. Several of the main roles are played by actual Nisei members of the 442nd, lending a beautiful authenticity to the storytelling. "Go for Broke" represents a landmark in the portrayal of Japanese-Americans in Hollywood films and is a must watch for WWII history and war movie buffs alike.

programme.title: Divorce of Lady X
programme.desc: With a grade-A cast led by the legendary dream team of Merle Oberon and Laurence Olivier (before he was “sir”), stylish direction by Tim Whelan (“The Thief of Baghdad”) and the highly capable production hand of the legendary Alexander Korda, “The Divorce of Lady X” is a film lover’s dream come true. Witty and charming, the film tells the story of a handsome divorce lawyer (Olivier) who shares a suite one night with an alluring guest at a costume party (Oberon), only to discover that she may be the erring wife of his new client.

programme.title: Valley of Vengeance
programme.desc: LUST FOR GOLD BROUGHT MASSACRE TO HUNDREDS! Death Rode the Plains! Directed by Sam Newfield (State Department: File 649) and starring Buster Crabbe (Flash Gordon) and Al St. John (Billy the Kid Trapped), Valley of Vengeance opens with Billy Carson (Crabbe) shooting two affluential town officials after they - and a band of outlaws - had murdered his and Fuzzy’s (St. John) parents years earlier. Arrested for the shootings, Billy tells the story of the outlaws killing his parents and the events that led to his shooting the town officials. Will Billy be able to prove his innocence and bring and end to the corrupted officials?

programme.title: Badman's Gold
programme.desc: After a series of robberies on stagecoaches carrying gold to the U.S. Mint, Sheriff Masters (Vern Teters) calls for the help of Johnny Carpenter to find the stolen gold and bring the outlaws to justice. To help him find the gold, Johnny enlists the aid of Bess Benson (Alyn Lockwood) and her brother Bob (Clarke Stevens) as well as Bess’ dog, Daisy. Directed by Robert Emmett Tansey, this film reminds viewers: RED-HOT GUNS SPIT WHITE-HOT LEAD!

programme.title: Quicksand (1950)
programme.desc: Mickey Rooney gives one of his greatest performances as mechanic Dan Brady, a desperate young man out to impress Vera, a sexy bottle blond who dreams of diamonds and furs. Feeling too light in the pocket to show her a good time, Dan embarks on a series of petty crimes to raise money. Dan finds himself in more trouble than he'd bargained for, and gradually sinks into the very quicksand of the film's title. Add Peter Lorre as one of Dan's seedy connections, and a dazzling Jeanne Cagney as the femme fatale, and you have the ingredients for a suspenseful baby noir, well-worth its cult following.

programme.title: Dick Tracy's Dilemma (1947)
programme.desc: In "Dick Tracy's Dilemma," Tracy is after a group of fur thieves who empty a dealer's vault and leaves a dead night guard at the scene. Tracy's investigation reveals the crimes were committed by an ex-con with a bum leg and a missing hand known as "The Claw." Ralph Byrd stars as Dick Tracy, reprising the role when exhibitors insisted he return after Morgan Conway played Tracy in two previous films. Filled with noir elements and suspenseful moments, "Dick Tracy's Dilemma" is an old-school classic.

programme.title: Blue Steel (1934)
programme.desc: Undercover US Marshal John Carruthers (John Wayne) is investigating a rash of robberies by a character known as "The Polka Dot Bandit" in this B-movie gem. Along the way, Carruthers finds himself in more trouble than he'd ever expected! Written and directed by Robert N. Bradbury, the film features George "Gabby" Hayes, Eleanor Hunt, and many other favorites of the era. Wayne was only 27 at the time of Blue Steel, but was well on his way to becoming "The Duke."

programme.title: Nosferatu
programme.desc: In this iconic German Expressionist horror film, F.W. Murnau adapts Bram Stoker's 1897 classic vampire novel Dracula.

programme.title: Nosferatu the Vampyre
programme.desc: From the distinct and enigmatic imagination of director Werner Herzog, Nosferatu the Vampyre stars Klaus Kinski and Isabelle Adjani in a retelling of F.W. Murnau's 1922 Dracula adaptation Nosferatu.

programme.title: Teenagers from Outer Space
programme.desc: A young alien and a teenage earthling fall in love, and plot to stop the alien's race from using Earth as a food-breeding ground for giant lobsters from their planet.

programme.title: Little Shop of Horrors
programme.desc: If you're young enough, this tale of a man-eating plant might scare you. If you're old enough, it'll make you laugh. Little Shop of Horrors is the insane story of lonely florist Seymour (Jonathan Haze) and his hungry plant, Audrey. Seymour will go to great lengths to make sure Audrey is fed and happy. With a cast that includes Dick Miller, Jackie Joseph, and a very young Jack Nicholson as a scene stealing dental patient, director Roger Corman and screenwriter Charles Griffith give us a comic horror masterpiece for the ages!

programme.title: Invisible Ghost (1941)
programme.desc: Bela Lugosi headlines this creepy thriller about an influential man who becomes a bloodthirsty maniac after his wife deserts him. It was the first of nine films made by Lugosi for Sam Katzman of Monogram Pictures, but it’s director Joseph H. Lewis (Gun Crazy, The Big Combo) who elevates this low budget potboiler into something memorable. Aided by veteran cinematographers Harvey Gould and Marcel Le Picard, Lewis creates the perfect atmosphere for this tale of a murderer who strikes in the night and leaves no clues...

programme.title: Creature from the Haunted Sea (1961)
programme.desc: Here’s another Roger Corman classic from the golden age of Drive-In schlock! In this spoof of horror and spy thrillers, American gangster Renzo Capetto (Anthony Carbone) decides to kill members of his bungling crew and blame their deaths on a legendary sea creature. What he doesn’t know is that the creature is actually out there!

programme.title: Sci-Fi Trailers - GORGO & TARGET EARTH
programme.desc: Trailers for two 1950 Sci-Fi classics Gorgo and Target Earth.

programme.title: Gorgo
programme.desc: Greedy sailors tangle with and capture Gorgo, a giant lizard, off the coast of Ireland and sell him to a London circus. Gorgo's mother, mad with rage, follows his trail to London leaving a wake of destruction in her path.

programme.title: White Zombie (1932)
programme.desc: Watch Bela Lugosi use his special zombie grip to make beautiful women submit to his every desire! In this low budget screamer, a couple honeymooning in Haiti run afoul of a diabolical voodoo master. They’re soon wishing they’d gone to Cancun! This Pre-­Code horror classic is considered to be the first feature length zombie movie, and features great atmospheric direction by Victor Halperin. The film’s unsung hero was set designer Ralph Berger, who exploited sets of previous Universal Studios films, including bits from Dracula, The Hunchback of Notre Dame, and Frankenstein. Whatever you do, DON’T LOOK INTO LUGOSI’S EYES!

programme.title: The Sadist
programme.desc: Written and directed by James Landis, this thriller loosely follows the story of the killing spree of Charles Starkweather (later films Badlands, 1973, and Natural Born Killers, 1994, were also based on Starkweather’s tale). Starring Arch Hall, Jr. The Sadist begins with three high school teachers driving through California. Unfortunately, their car breaks down in an abandoned area, where they experience a run in with a bloodthirsty sadist and his girlfriend. A truly terrifying experience, this film will have you on the edge of your seat from start to finish!

programme.title: Scared To Death
programme.desc: The only color film to star Bela Lugosi was this mystery thriller from director Christy Cabanne (The Mummy’s Hand) made for the short­lived Golden Gate Pictures during the early months of 1946. Lugosi plays Professor Leonide, a cagy character who may have had something to do with the death of a young woman (who happens to be telling her tale from a slab at the morgue!). George Zucco, Molly Lamont, and Joyce Compton also star, as well as Angelo Rossitto, (Freaks) as a menacing dwarf with a habit of stepping on Lugosi’s foot!

programme.title: She Gods of Shark Reef
programme.desc: Two brothers, including one wanted for murder, are shipwrecked on an island inhabited by beautiful woman who possess a cache of valuable pearls. What the brothers don't know is that the island women worship a shark god, and are known to make human sacrifices! With a cast that includes the smoldering Lisa Montell, this intense adventure was directed by drive-in movie king Roger Corman. For movie buffs: Corman made the most of location shooting, filming Shark Reef in the same Hawaiian setting as Naked Paradise (1957).

programme.title: Mesa of Lost Women
programme.desc: Spider-women lure men to their death in this thriller from the golden era of Drive-in schlock! This story of a mad scientist (Jackie Coogan) is regarded as one of the worst movies ever made. Still, dig the crazy guitar and piano score which was purloined by Ed Wood Jr. for Jail Bait, and notice a couple of Wood regulars (Dolores Fuller and Lyle Talbot) in the credits. What you have here is a sort of cousin to the films of Ed Wood, but one that can stand on its own as being truly awful. Enjoy!

programme.title: The Brain That Wouldn't Die (1962)
programme.desc: While driving to his family’s country house, Dr. Bill Cortner (Jason Evers) and his fiancée, Jan Compton (Virginia Leith) get into a horrible car accident, leaving Jan decapitated. An expert in transplants, Dr. Cortner rushes to his lab with Jan’s severed head, and searches for a way to save his fiancée. Keeping her head alive in a liquid-filled tray, Dr. Cortner searches for a woman to murder in the hope that he may transplant Jan’s head onto a new body. His efforts lead to chaotic results. Written and directed by Joseph Green, this 1962 flick will be sure to keep you at the edge of your seat from beginning to end!

programme.title: House On Haunted Hill
programme.desc: A millionaire offers ten thousand dollars to five people if they agree to stay overnight in a large, spooky, rented house. When you consider that the millionaire is Vincent Price, and the film is directed by schlock master William Castle, you can bet the five guests are in for a long, bumpy night. This "super shocker of the century" was a smash hit upon its 1959 release. For architecture buffs, the home used for the exteriors of the haunted house was actually designed by Frank Lloyd Wright and built in 1924!

programme.title: Carnival of Souls (1962)

The sole survivor of the accident, Mary, accepts a job in a new town as a church organist where she is repeatedly troubled by visions of a nearby abandoned carnival and a smiling white-faced man with dark rimmed eyes. One of the most atmospherically eerie works of American horror cinema, the film garnered a significant cult following years after being released in 1962, and is essential for every horror collection.

George Romero's "Night of the Living Dead" is hailed as one of the most influential horror films of all time - inspirational, thought provoking, and most importantly, terrifying!

programme.title: Her Story

Violet is drawn to Allie, a reporter who approaches her for an interview. Career-driven Paige meets James, the first man she's considered opening up to in years. Will they risk letting what they are stand in the way of being loved for who they are? This is a story of complex characters who laugh, struggle, and grow, who share strength in sisterhood, who seek and find love. Her Story depicts the unique, complicated, and very human women we see in queer communities, and explores how these women navigate the intersections of label identity and love.

programme.title: The Guys Next Door
programme.desc: Who, among us, can say that we come from a “normal” family? The Guys Next Door, a feature length documentary, offers an alternative to the traditional ideas of what constitute the nuclear American family. Meet Erik and Sandro, a gay couple with two daughters birthed by their friend Rachel with donor eggs. In her 40s, Rachel is married to Tony and they have three biological children of their own. Rachel and Tony, a seemingly traditional married couple, live in the suburbs of Massachusetts with their children. Inspired by a TV program about the difficulties and costs associated with gay couples having children, Rachel, age 41, volunteers to be a surrogate – not once, but twice within two years – for Erik, her good friend from college, and his husband Sandro, an Italian émigré. This film begins when Rachel is eight months pregnant with Erik and Sandro’s second daughter, Eleonora. What compels a woman in her forties with three children of her own to carry children for friends? What is the reaction of her husband and children? And, how will Erik and Sandro handle the challenges of parenting two girls in a world that still emphasizes the importance of maternal instinct? The issues raised in this film - gay marriage and parenting, surrogacy as a path for gays and lesbians to have children, and the extension and redefinition of what it means to be “an American family" - remain relevant as our country is a cultural battleground during the divisive 2016 presidential election. The Guys Next Door is a powerful antidote to the negative backlash and hateful rhetoric aimed at same sex families. In the words of the esteemed documentary filmmaker Ross McElwee (Sherman’s March), “with nuance, verve and humor, this film goes well beyond issues of surrogacy and gay parenthood and explores the humanity that connects us all."

programme.title: A Very Sordid Wedding
programme.desc: Seventeen years after family matriarch Peggy tripped over G.W.’s wooden legs in Sordid Lives, same-sex marriage equality has barreled into Winters, Texas and not everyone is ready to accept it. An anniversary memorial service is being planned in honor of Peggy at the bar while the Southside Baptist Church plans an "Anti-Equality" rally to protest the abomination of gay marriage and work to defend their religious freedom. The beloved cast of colorful characters are all on a collision course for shenanigans and fireworks on the big night. Along the way a bisexual serial killer shows up, a drag queen country medley is performed and a beauty-salon-versus-the-bigots battle turns getting your hair done into the front lines of the equality battle. Friendships are tested and families are reunited as fear and bigotry are confronted with acceptance and understanding on the way to a surprise wedding with (almost) everyone in attendance.

programme.title: Braking For Whales
programme.desc: Star and Brandon, estranged brother and sister, are brought together after their mother's recent death and her absurd final request to dispose of her ashes in the body of a whale. With no choice or face losing their much-needed inheritance - they embark on a road trip to San Antonio, Texas where they not only encounter adventure, but also encounter each other. Braking For Whales stars Tom Felton, Tammin Sursok, Wendi Mclendon-Covey, David Koechner, and Austin Swift.

programme.title: I'm From Driftwood
programme.desc: James Clementi Chooses Compassion And Activism After Brother's Death/Man With Cerebral Palsy Recalls First Experience At Gay Bar/Men Are Gay Because They Like Men, You Should Think About Putting On A Little Muscle Next Time/Mom, I’m Gay, Own A Porn Company And Am In A Polyamorous Relationship/Queer, Sexual And Proud, Right Out Of The Womb/Soccer Mom Takes Tomboy To The Gap To Fix Their Gender/The Challenges Of Gender Expression In The Workplace/Transgender Lesbian: I Took A Brave Step To Ensure That I Live In The Light Of Truth/Transgender Man Comes Out To Girlfriend/Transgender Man's Visit To Barbershop Marks New Chapter In Life/Will McGinn: I'm From Staten Island NY - True Gay Stories S1 E21-31 | After the tragic death of his brother Tyler, James decides to live a life of compassion and activism. Andrew, who has Cerebral Palsy and uses a wheelchair, remembers the excitement of going to a gay bar for the first time and the reality that sets in once he arrives. Jason was a ballet dancer during most of his teenage years and into his 20s. He was celebrated for being thin. During one of his first times at a gay bar, he was told he's too skinny and needed to put on some muscle, leading him down a path of taking testosterone and being unhappy. It wasn't until he realized he needed to be happy with who he was because "I wasn’t happy pretending to be someone else." Growing up in a religious household, Benjamine was concerned about having to come out to his mom not only as gay, but as the owner of the successful porn company CockyBoys and being in a polyamorous relationship with two other guys. What he learned from the experience was that “honestly is the best thing in life.” At 5 years old, Noah Michelson did a seductive dance in his underwear for the family's garbage man. After being called "queer", Noah finally had a word to define who he was and how he felt. Renee has always been a tomboy, and now identifies as queer. When Renee was a teen, a neighborhood mom noticed how Renee dressed and took them (Renee uses "they/them/their" pronouns) to The Gap to buy them feminine-looking pants. The experience was traumatic, but also transformational. From wearing Catholic school uniforms in childhood to menswear at a global bank, Erika Miguel has been all over the spectrum of gender expression and fashion. An inappropriate encounter at her job, related to her gender expression, led her to find a new job. Tori Baker went from a rough childhood to drugs to having a daughter and turning her life around. The turning point was realizing that she "can be who I am and like the people that I like.” Mitch was afraid that the relationship might end, but knew it was time to tell his girlfriend that he's transgender. Not only did she support him, they're relationship grew stronger and eventually got married/ Only a few months before a study abroad trip to Rome, Charlie had begun hormone therapy and completed top surgery. He was nervous--about the language barrier and about passing as a male--when he walked into a small barbershop in Rome. Coming out leads to some embarrassing questions from this young man's mom.

programme.title: Political Animals
programme.desc: Political Animals celebrates the legendary civil rights victories of four trailblazing California state politicians: Carole Migden, Sheila Keuhl, Jackie Goldberg, and Christine Kehoe. Fierce and unrelenting, these courageous women toppled a partisan majority and emerged victors to pass historic legislation for social justice and LGBT+ equality. It was a hard fight – filled with vehemently heated debates and hateful insults hurled by opponents. Today, the message behind Political Animals is more important than ever as the current political theatre unfurls around the globe. These inspiring biographies further reveal the critical importance for public resistance at the local level to pressure lawmakers to enact difficult change. Political Animals is a clear call to action for a new era of greater democratic participation. We invite you to follow in the footsteps of these historic leaders and become the next pioneering political animal!

Andrew, who has Cerebral Palsy and uses a wheelchair, remembers the excitement of going to a gay bar for the first time and the reality that sets in once he arrives. Jason was a ballet dancer during most of his teenage years and into his 20s. He was celebrated for being thin. During one of his first times at a gay bar, he was told he's too skinny and needed to put on some muscle, leading him down a path of taking testosterone and being unhappy. It wasn't until he realized he needed to be happy with who he was because "I wasn’t happy pretending to be someone else." Growing up in a religious household, Benjamine was concerned about having to come out to his mom not only as gay, but as the owner of the successful porn company CockyBoys and being in a polyamorous relationship with two other guys. What he learned from the experience was that “honestly is the best thing in life.” At 5 years old, Noah Michelson did a seductive dance in his underwear for the family's garbage man. After being called "queer", Noah finally had a word to define who he was and how he felt. Renee has always been a tomboy, and now identifies as queer. When Renee was a teen, a neighborhood mom noticed how Renee dressed and took them (Renee uses "they/them/their" pronouns) to The Gap to buy them feminine-looking pants. The experience was traumatic, but also transformational. From wearing Catholic school uniforms in childhood to menswear at a global bank, Erika Miguel has been all over the spectrum of gender expression and fashion. An inappropriate encounter at her job, related to her gender expression, led her to find a new job. Tori Baker went from a rough childhood to drugs to having a daughter and turning her life around. The turning point was realizing that she "can be who I am and like the people that I like.” Mitch was afraid that the relationship might end, but knew it was time to tell his girlfriend that he's transgender. Not only did she support him, they're relationship grew stronger and eventually got married/ Only a few months before a study abroad trip to Rome, Charlie had begun hormone therapy and completed top surgery. He was nervous--about the language barrier and about passing as a male--when he walked into a small barbershop in Rome. Coming out leads to some embarrassing questions from this young man's mom.

programme.title: Political Animals
programme.desc: Political Animals celebrates the legendary civil rights victories of four trailblazing California state politicians: Carole Migden, Sheila Keuhl, Jackie Goldberg, and Christine Kehoe. Fierce and unrelenting, these courageous women toppled a partisan majority and emerged victors to pass historic legislation for social justice and LGBT+ equality. It was a hard fight – filled with vehemently heated debates and hateful insults hurled by opponents. Today, the message behind Political Animals is more important than ever as the current political theatre unfurls around the globe. These inspiring biographies further reveal the critical importance for public resistance at the local level to pressure lawmakers to enact difficult change. Political Animals is a clear call to action for a new era of greater democratic participation. We invite you to follow in the footsteps of these historic leaders and become the next pioneering political animal!

Followed for 8 years by filmmaker Harrod Blank (son of Les Blank), Rusty guides us through the aftermath of her transition. Interwoven with lively tales of gender non-conforming individuals on the art-car circuit, Blank’s film is a sensitive and unpredictable love letter to people who fight to be unapologetically themselves.

programme.title: The Millennial Experience
programme.desc: The Millennial Experience is one part dance-for-film and one part documentary. The film explores cultural appropriation vs appreciation, LGBTQIA+ culture, feminism and how these topics impact the Millennial generation. The dance sequences in the film are adapted from director Alex Crozier's stage production MILLENNIALS which focuses on the aforementioned themes. Fourteen on-camera interviews that expound on the main topics were conducted with people of various ages, ethnicities, sexual orientations, and genders . The Millennial Experience seeks to uplift the voices of women, LGBTQIA+, and BIPOC communities in an effort to create a more equitable and just world.

programme.title: Strut
programme.desc: In each episode of Strut, we watch Eddie and her friends transform through their risky new endeavor in unexpected positive ways. Eddie is a geeky porn editor whose low self-confidence has turned her into a 26-year-old hermit. Her friends, Eva (an unemployed artist), Lucy (an intern), and Chandaleer (a trainwreck/fashion model) vow to save her from her unhealthy solitude. When the friends decide to start a high-end escorting agency to earn more money, they convince skeptical Eddie to help them build their business and lift her self-esteem. Together they successfully navigate the adrenaline-fueled escorting industry with Eddie as their CEO and fellow sex worker.

programme.title: Moving Stories
programme.desc: A film, by Rob Fruchtman, Cornelia Ravenal, Mikael Södersten, Wendy Sax Six, about diverse dancers from the acclaimed Battery Dance Company who travel the world, working with youth who have experienced war, poverty, prejudice, sexual exploitation, and severe trauma as refugees. In India they work with girls rescued from sex trafficking and gender violence; in Romania, with gypsy kids from one of Europe's worst slums; in South Korea, with young North Koreans who risked their lives to escape; and in Iraq, with a gifted young Muslim dancer, fighting to survive. Incredibly, they have just one week to teach the tools of choreography and collaboration to kids who may be enemies, who may have been abused, who may be suspicious and fearful, so that they can create dances to perform for their communities. As they struggle to break through, the dancer-teachers confront their own frustrations. Yet their students respond in extraordinary ways - and as they prepare to perform in public in what seems an impossibly short time, both students and teachers experience surprising transformations, unlocking feelings and stories in wellsprings of creativity.

programme.title: The Dead Mothers Club
programme.desc: The (Dead Mothers) Club tells the story of three women- a Southern artist redefining herself through her art; a high school senior struggling to gain independence; and a Brazilian living in NY, navigating first-time motherhood – all of whom lost their mothers during adolescence. The film reveals how coming of age without their mothers has and continues to play a role in their lives. Structured around a series of ‘dialogues’ featuring Rosie O’Donnell, Molly Shannon and Jane Fonda that focus on various themes threading their stories together, these ruminations allow for heart-breaking and at times humorous insight into how ultimately one’s past can dictate their future. From the cyclical nature of grief to their own mortality, the women of The Club provoke thoughts surrounding the innate, complicated nature of the mother/daughter relationship, even in its absence.

programme.title: Kumu Hina
programme.desc: Imagine a world where a little boy can grow up to be the woman of his dreams, and a young girl can rise to become a leader among men. Welcome to Kumu Hina's Hawai'i. Kumu Hina tells the inspiring story of Hina Wong-Kalu, a transgender native Hawaiian teacher, or kumu, who brings to life Hawai‘i's traditional embrace of mahu - those who embody both male and female spirit. Produced by Emmy-winning directors Dean Hamer and Joe Wilson in association with ITVS and Pacifc Islanders in Communications, the film traces Hina's evolution from Collin Wong, a timid high school boy, to her present position as a married woman and cultural director of a school in one of Honolulu's grittier neighborhoods. When Ho‘onani, a charismatic 6th grade girl, asks to join the school's all-male hula troupe, Kumu Hina gives her the opportunity to express her inner male spirit. As teacher and student prepare for a climactic end-of-year public performance, they meet many obstacles, but hold fast to the idea that being true to oneself matters most.

They are flying high from their ride with the Hells Angels, but the high-speeds are causing dissension among the members - and Kevin turns in his colors. A visit to historic Tombstone gives Baker pause and makes him re-think the ICMFH patch and asks the members to vote on giving it up. Is this the end of the club?

programme.title: Stepdads The Sketch- Ep 1
programme.desc: When infidelity claims the life of Joanne Bates, her children Lisa and Stevie are left in the custody of her fiancé Mike and his brother Jerry. Mike, a straight-laced, hardworking accountant; and Jerry, a wild, unstable, womanizer were both former foster children and together they provide a unique balance of parenting skills for young Lisa and Stevie. - Step Dads starring Ben Sloane (R.I.P.D, Alpha House), Morocco Omari (Empire, 21 Bridges, Homeland, Chicago Fire), Jorie Binion (Chicago P.D) Charles Dunlap (Chicago Fire, Empire), and Jay Davis (Not Another Black Movie, Choke On That: The Series, Not Another Zombie Movie) is a comedy about two polar opposite foster brothers raising two children using non-traditional parenting methods while shedding a satirical light on the importance of adoption. We poke fun at some of the mishaps which comes along with the shock of being a new parent, but ultimately, we hope to spread awareness on adoption, the importance of having fathers and father-figures in the lives of young people, and having a familial loving environment. The moral of our story is that “No family is perfect, but every child deserves to be loved unconditionally, and raised in a reliable, stable support system.”

programme.desc: Dr. Proctor is a geoscientist, explorer, space artist, and astronaut. She is the mission pilot for the Inspiration4 all-civilian orbital mission to space. She is also one of The Explorer’s Club 50: Fifty People Changing the World. Her motto is called Space2inspire where she encourages people to use their unique, one-of-a-kind strengths, and passion to inspire those within their reach and beyond. She believes that we need to actively strive for a J.E.D.I. space: a just, equitable, diverse, and inclusive space as we advance human spaceflight.

programme.title: Europa
programme.desc: Discovering and exploring Jupiter's most promising moon, Europa. Europa was named after a Phoenician noblewoman who was abducted by Zeus after he had transformed himself into a bull. Rather fittingly, Zeus established Europa on the island of Crete as its queen, where he had several children with her, including Minos, the legendary king of Crete. In later ages, the continent of Europe would be named after Europa.

programme.title: My Hometown Favorites
programme.desc: New York, NY: Passionate about his city, Tony gives us an intimate tour of the New York City foods he loves - sturgeon and bagels, fluke ceviche, pan-seared foie gras, braised veal cheek, authentic cheese and, of course, a hotdog.

programme.title: Curbside Eats
programme.desc: Join hosts Maya Norman and Katrina Kozar as they travel in an R.V. for good food, good drink, and great conversation on Curbside Eats.

programme.title: Best Freaks of Nature
programme.desc: If you like your nature a little weird, then this is the show for you. See all the freaks of nature in the best parks ever.

programme.title: Hottest Parks
programme.desc: Volcanoes erupt and geysers explode in this sizzling episode. Take a look at the hottest parks you can visit!

programme.title: S8E5 - Eat Like a Local in Los Cabos
programme.desc: Ever travel to a tourist mecca and wonder what the locals eat? Join Rick and his friend Hugo to find the best Mexican food in Los Cabos. First stop is the municipal market in San Jose del Cabo, then they enjoy carnitas at Los Michoacanos.

programme.title: New Releases
programme.desc: Check out some of our new content!

programme.title: Malta
programme.desc: A delightful Mediterranean climate, fantastic beaches, and fascinating historic sites only begin to describe the Maltese experience. Few places in the world possess a more exquisite coastline. The HBO series, "Game of Thrones," filmed portions of the series in Malta's capital city of Valletta.

programme.title: Florence
programme.desc: In this glorious Italian city, rich in history and art, Rudy brings the Renaissance to life. We visit the great museums - the Uffizi, Bargello, and Accademia, as well as the landmarks of the Renaissance - the Duomo, Baptistry and Giotto's Tower.

programme.title: Adelaide, Part 2
programme.desc: Captivated by South Australia's incredible beauty, Jason continues his Australian expedition along historic Hahndorf Main Street as he explores Adelaide’s Central Market and the Adelaide Festival Centre.

programme.title: S8E9 - Amsterdam
programme.desc: Uniquely entertaining Amsterdam shows off its Rembrandts and Van Goghs, rivers of bikes, and pot-filled coffeeshops — all under gabled facades leaning out over placid canals.

programme.title: Havana's Spirit
programme.desc: Cuban ingenuity and creativity are alive in Cuba’s capital of Havana, a UNESCO World Heritage Site. A leading site for fashion and music, Havana is reconnecting with its past as a starlet. Santiago de Cuba, the birthplace of Cuban music, is also featured. Experience “La Cubania.”

programme.title: St. Augustine
programme.desc: First, we will take a sip from the distinctively tasting Fountain of Youth. Then we will touch the coquina walls of the undefeated Castillo San Marcos. Next, separate pirate truth from pirate myth at the appropriately named, Pirate Museum, and cure what ails us at the oldest General Store.

programme.title: S7E5 - Florentine Delights and on exciting Tuscan Side Trips
programme.desc: We enjoy Renaissance art in Florence, the city that propelled Europe out of the Middle Ages. Then we visit two cultural capitals in their own right: Pisa, where we’ll marvel at a tipsy tower; and Lucca, where we’ll celebrate Puccini.

programme.title: Deep Sea Corals of Polynesia
programme.desc: Join the U.T.P. team to the Polynesian Islands as they lead a scientific team to unveil the coral reefs of the deep. After setting new records in diving within Arctic waters, Ghislain and Emmanuelle Bardout study how these reefs function, with the hope of capturing on film the corals spawning.

programme.title: Chinguetti
programme.desc: Once at a crossroads of ancient trade routes, the ksar of Chinguetti, Mauritania exists like a pearl in the desert on the western edge of the Sahara Desert, a force of nature whose sand reaches every crook and crevice of life in this land.

programme.title: Tamales and Iguana, Oaxacan Style
programme.desc: Oaxaca, Mexico: Chef Tony Bourdain explores the exotic and colorful indigenous zone of Mexico's Oaxaca region where he tastes toasted grasshoppers and other delicacies. His adventure ends with mariachi music and, of course, lots of tequila.

programme.title: Cod Crazy
programme.desc: Portugal: Portuguese cuisine holds a dear place in Tony's culinary heart. Tony travels to Porto, home of the famous Port wine, where he is immediately exposed to the codfish and the almost mythical place it holds in Portuguese cuisine and culture.

programme.title: San Francisco
programme.desc: Stroll down Grant Street with Laura into the heart of America's largest Chinatown. Bike, drive, or walk across the Golden Gate Bridge, the city's most recognizable landmark. Finally, Fisherman's Wharf offers day trips all wrapped into one fun location.

programme.title: Versailles
programme.desc: Enter 12 miles of enclosing walls, 26 acres of roof, and over 2,000 windows and experience the royal Palace of Versailles. If you are looking for some good ole' fun, then you will enjoy Parc Asterix. Place Vendome is the top spot for high-end merchandise.

programme.title: Gold Coast Australia
programme.desc: If you like sun, surf, sand, and a laid-back lifestyle then join Laura on Australia's Gold Coast. Travel into the thick of the Queensland Rainforest, and visit the home of the largest collection of Australian native animals in the Carrumbin Wildlife Sanctuary.

programme.title: Sicily
programme.desc: Begin on the east coast in Taormina. Laura then takes us to some of Sicily's highlight cities, Palermo and Randazzo. How about a visit to Agrigento, or to the divinely inspired Cathedral Monreale? We will also visit Mt. Etna, an active volcano.

programme.title: Venice
programme.desc: Begin with a tour down the Grand Canal, "the finest street in the world." Next, the pedestrian streets around the Rialto Bridge are lined with shops, and St. Mark's Basilica is one of the oldest and most beautiful Byzantine cathedrals in all of Europe.

programme.title: Oahu, Hawaii
programme.desc: Have a blast with Laura on this Hawaiian voyage as you explore sensational surf and beaches, unique Hawaiian culture and food, and climb volcanic mountains. Join Laura as she visits historic landmarks, such as the Iolani Palace and the Bishop Museum.

programme.title: Italy: Part 1
programme.desc: Experience the arresting appeal and elegance of Italy in six select locations. Take an invigorating stroll along the Mediterranean coast in Castello Federiciano, marvel at Alberobello’s august trullo dry stone huts, and more.

programme.title: Shedd Aquarium: Wild Reef
programme.desc: Experience the wonder of the Shedd Aquarium’s wild reef as light dances off the colorful aquatic sea life that peacefully swim past in the crystal-clear water. Ambient sound makes you feel as if you are deep beneath the ocean.

programme.title: Village of Swimming Cows
programme.desc: What happens when eco-minded, city-dwelling Berliners move in with Polish farmers in the country? Take a charming, extraordinarily funny look at how friendship and communication can overcome boundaries, and how nourishing the mind, body, and spirit begins with love and respect for Mother Earth.

programme.title: Papua New Guinea: The Fire Dance
programme.desc: When a person dies, or to celebrate a harvest or important visit, the Baining tribesmen create masks representing the Spirit of the Forest. A great fire is then lit in the village, and dancers adorning the masks dance around the fire, jumping on the embers to prove they are stronger than the flames.

programme.title: Peru: Masters of Chaos
programme.desc: Anthropologist Anne-Sylvie Malbrancke journeys to meet Jenny, a young Peruvian who has crossed the country to ask the sacred lakes to heal her medical issue. For more than 700 years, shamans have drawn their power to heal from the Huaringas, sacred lagoons located on the border of Peru and Ecuador.

programme.title: Amazonia: Becoming a Man
programme.desc: In the heart of the Amazon rainforest of Brazil, the Satere-Mawe people have a rite of passage leading to adulthood where a feat of bravery turns boys into men. According to tribe members, this painful initiation prepares young men for life and proves they can fulfill their reproductive obligations.

programme.title: Running of the Bulls
programme.desc: The Festival of San Fermin in Pamplona, Spain is a deeply rooted celebration of traditional and folkloric events, including the Running of the Bulls. Experience the incredible energy each morning for eight consecutive days as thousands of people run ahead of six, 2,000-pound charging bulls.

programme.title: S8E1 - Mediterranean Baja
programme.desc: The Baja California peninsula boasts a climate reminiscent of the Mediterranean Sea. Rick makes tacos with ingredients from the gardens of the Rancho La Puerta spa, and meets up with Chefs Miguel Angel Guerrero Yagues and Jair Tellez.

programme.title: S8E2 - Tijuana Taco Crawl
programme.desc: Three local Tijuana foodies take Rick on a taco crawl. Experience arrachera tacos, suadero tacos, sauteed and fried shrimp tacos, steamed tacos, and smoked salmon tacos. At home, Rick creates a taco feast for a casual backyard cookout.

programme.title: S8E3 - Cooking on the Sea of Cortez
programme.desc: Rick is always up for a cooking challenge, and after a day on the waters of the Sea of Cortez, Rick grills dinner for the group on the beach of Espiritu Santo Island. To stock up on supplies Rick shops in the La Paz market for ingredients.

programme.title: S8E4 - Presenting: World-Class Wines of Baja
programme.desc: Join Rick and winemaker Hugo d’Acosta as they toast the world-class wines of Baja California Norte. Hugo first introduces Rick his Casa de Piedra wines before moving on to Tres Mujeres, L.A. Cetto, and the San Rafael Winery.

programme.title: S8E5 - Eat Like a Local in Los Cabos
programme.desc: Ever travel to a tourist mecca and wonder what the locals eat? Join Rick and his friend Hugo to find the best Mexican food in Los Cabos. First stop is the municipal market in San Jose del Cabo, then they enjoy carnitas at Los Michoacanos.

programme.title: S8E6 - A Delicious Feast in Magdalena Bay
programme.desc: Rick and local guide Luis Garduno of REDTours venture out on a skiff to learn about sustainable fishing on Magdalena Bay. They catch up with local lobster fishermen and clam divers and follow that up with shore lunch on Isla de Magdalena.

programme.title: S8E7 - Cooking in Wine Country
programme.desc: Ever dream of owning a winery? Don and Tru Miller made their dreams come true when they built Adobe Guadalupe. Rick’s dream of cooking in their stunning kitchen, with its handmade wood-fired oven, comes true this season. Dream on.

programme.title: S8E8 - Tijuana Round Table
programme.desc: There is a long heritage of good food in Tijuana. The city has an amazing taco, culture and is the birthplace of the Caesar salad. Today, Tijuana boasts one of the top culinary schools in the country and some of the best chefs in Mexico.

programme.title: S8E9 - Extraordinarily Delicious Ensenada
programme.desc: Fish tacos embody Ensenada’s history: Fresh fish from pristine waters encased in crispy batter influenced by Asian immigrants, topped with Spanish-inspired creamy sauces, wrapped in a very Mexican corn tortilla, and spiked with chile.

programme.title: S8E10 - Mexican Microbrews and Pub Fare
programme.desc: Many of us experienced our first Mexican beer on a beach with a squeeze of lime. Now we are happy to see a beer revolution rumbling in the Baja peninsula. Rick takes us from the Tecate brewery to the Tijuana brewery. Salud-

programme.title: S8E11 - Sustainable Aquaculture in the Rich Waters of Ensenada
programme.desc: Two of Ensenada’s best chefs, Benito Molina, and Alain Genchi, join Rick for a lesson in mollusk farming. Juan Carlos Lapuente takes the trio to the rich coastal waters to see oyster and mussel farming and learn why these waters thrive.

programme.title: S8E12 - Todos Santos Magic
programme.desc: There is magic in the charming Baja town of Todos Santos. It all starts at the roadside bar Art and Beer. Then Rick checks into the Hotel California before meeting with Sergio Jaurequi, as well as Chefs Dona Ramona and Dany Lamote.

programme.title: S8E13 - Baja Beach House Cooking
programme.desc: Rick introduces us to some of Los Cabos’ top chefs and their restaurants, then cooks dinner for them at a luxurious beach house. At dinner, Rick, Margarita, and the local chefs discuss the philosophy of cooking and dining together.

programme.title: S9E1 - Oaxaca's Most Magical Holiday
programme.desc: Rick takes us on a remarkable journey through Oaxaca City during the revered Dia de Los Muertos (Day of the Dead) holiday. Much preparation for the celebration takes place in October, and Rick gives us an insider’s look at the fiesta.

programme.title: S9E2 - Oaxaca's Live-Fire Cooking
programme.desc: Everything tastes better when cooked over a fire, at least that is the Oaxacan credo. From soup to barbacoa, fiery embers influence the flavor of Oaxaca’s food in just the right ways. Join Rick in Oaxaca, San Felipe Usila, and Zaachilla.

programme.title: S9E3 - Off the Beaten Path in Huatulco
programme.desc: Mexico's beaches glimmer with pristine perfection. Chef Rick Bayless takes us off the beaten path to find great food and even better beaches such as Playa Chahue and Playa Principal. You would be well-advised to follow his lead.

programme.title: S9E4 - Artisan Mescal
programme.desc: Mescal is experiencing a renaissance in Mexico and throughout the United States. Journey with Rick to witness firsthand how an Oaxacan distiller handcrafts this fine spirit renowned for its rich, smoky complexity and brightness.

programme.title: S9E5 - Oaxaca, the Land of Seven Moles
programme.desc: So many moles, so little time. Rick will focus on two moles while visiting the Seasons of My Heart Cooking School on the outskirts of Oaxaca City to explore Black Mole and Green Mole with school owner Susana Trilling and her students.

programme.title: S9E6 - Delicious Eco-Tourism
programme.desc: Ever on a quest to learn more about food, Rick even vacations with a food-oriented agenda. Join him in the mountains of Finca Las Nieves, with its artisanal coffee production and organic gardens, and learn about sustainable gardening.

programme.title: S9E7 - The Kernel of Deliciousness
programme.desc: The variety of corns available in Oaxaca boggles the mind and the taste buds. Rick introduces us to Amado Ramirez Leyva who believes that corn, domesticated some 9,000 years ago in Mexico, represents the very foundation of Mexican culture.

programme.title: S9E8 - Mercado Madness
programme.desc: “You are what you eat.” Brillat Savarin’s statement fuels Rick’s tour of the 21 de Noviembre market in downtown Oaxaca. We uncover the incredibly rich culture of the market and its role in the daily lives and meals of the local population.

programme.title: S9E9 - Oaxacan Cheese Primer
programme.desc: In Mexico, cheese is all about freshness, and fresh cheese is exactly what Rick has found in the village of Rojas where he and two local women turn uber-fresh milk from alfalfa-fed cows into queso fresco and salty quesillo (string cheese).

programme.title: S9E10 - Puerto Escondido: Living the Dream
programme.desc: Ever dream of renting a space with a kitchen in Mexico just to cook all the fresh fish you can eat? Rick lives the dream at Hotel Villas Carrizalillo in Puerto Escondido. With few culinary tools, and fresh ingredients, it is time to feast.

programme.title: S9E11 - Chocolate & Coffee from Bean to Cup
programme.desc: In Mexico, hot chocolate and coffee are equally enjoyed. The Seasons of My Heart Cooking School explains the roasting process from two perspectives, while the Finca Las Nieves Coffee Plantation offers a look into organic coffee production.

programme.title: S9E12 - Bringing Oaxaca Home
programme.desc: The once unknown state of Oaxaca is now on the savvy traveler’s hit list. Its capital is one of Mexico’s most enjoyable colonial cities. Rick takes the spirit of Oaxaca home, and with a group of friends, creates a dinner sure to transport.

programme.title: S9E13 - Oaxaca's Top Chefs
programme.desc: Oaxaca has long been known for its seven moles, unparalleled home-cooking, and remarkable market fare. Lately, its restaurant reputation has skyrocketed, too. Deservedly so. Rick visits four of the top chef contenders in Oaxaca City.

programme.title: My Hometown Favorites
programme.desc: New York, NY: Passionate about his city, Tony gives us an intimate tour of the New York City foods he loves - sturgeon and bagels, fluke ceviche, pan-seared foie gras, braised veal cheek, authentic cheese and, of course, a hotdog.

programme.title: San Sebastian: A Food Lover's Town
programme.desc: San Sebastian, Spain: Tony explores the food-crazed Basque culture. Tony's guide, Chef Luis Irizar, takes Tony into the underworld of Basque gastronomic societies. Later, Tony explores the city's tapas bars.

programme.title: Saigon
programme.desc: Saigon, Vietnam is an incredible place to visit. It has history, and cultural excursions, like cruising the Mekong Delta and visiting a floating marketplace. In Ho Chi Minh City you can shop until you drop, stay in five-star hotels, and enjoy an incredible culinary experience.

programme.title: Auckland
programme.desc: Auckland is New Zealand's largest city. Laura takes an hour's drive south of Auckland to a working sheep farm in the New Zealand countryside. A few miles down the road, Laura spies a familiar sight - Hobbiton, the set from the Lord of the Rings films where Bilbo lived before and after his journey.

programme.title: Athens
programme.desc: Athens is an exceptional country to experience history. First, visit Syntagma Square and Greece's famous landmark- The Acropolis. An excursion to Greece is nothing without a trip to the Agora, as we finish off by enjoying Athens’ most abundant resource- water.

programme.title: Singapore
programme.desc: The first sight is Singapore's Merlion statue. For glimpses of the wild you have three fun options where you can see exotic animals in their open (not closed) sanctuaries. Next, explore Raffles Landing for a picture-perfect view along the Singapore River.

programme.title: Naples
programme.desc: Naples exists in an incredible location at the base of Mt. Vesuvius beside the Port of Naples. Experience Napoli's castles on the islet of Megaris, Castel dell 'Ovo, Castel Nuovo, Castel Saint Elmo, Arch of Triumph of Alfonso, and the Torre dell' Oro.

programme.title: Gleneagles & Scottish Countryside
programme.desc: First, head over to Castle Rock. Then, venture down to the Royal Mile that provides fascinating insights into the region's history, and is a charming street of pubs, restaurants, and shops. Also, take a moment to revel in the glory of St Giles' Cathedral.

programme.title: Italy: Part 1
programme.desc: Experience the arresting appeal and elegance of Italy in six select locations. Take an invigorating stroll along the Mediterranean coast in Castello Federiciano, marvel at Alberobello’s august trullo dry stone huts, and more.

programme.title: Shedd Aquarium: Underwater Beauty
programme.desc: Fish of all stripes and fluorescence call the crystal-clear waters of Chicago’s Shedd Aquarium home. Water and light collaborate to reveal the tranquil beauty that is life underwater.

programme.title: Village of Swimming Cows
programme.desc: What happens when eco-minded, city-dwelling Berliners move in with Polish farmers in the country? Take a charming, extraordinarily funny look at how friendship and communication can overcome boundaries, and how nourishing the mind, body, and spirit begins with love and respect for Mother Earth.

programme.title: Samoa: Tattoo Heritage
programme.desc: The tattooing practiced in Samoa is not comparable to the fashionable trend in Europe. In Samoa, tattooing is above all a rite signifying that the individual belongs to a group, and it is extremely painful. The more painful it is, the more Stivi approaches the state of a real, accomplished man.

programme.title: Haiti: The Carnival of Specters
programme.desc: Every year in Jacmel, on the southern coast of Haiti, festivities take on an intensity not found elsewhere. Haitians do not depict dream-like characters in their parades, but instead, monsters or specters. This is a way for them to deal with the difficulties of the past, and those of the present.

programme.title: India: Festival of Colors
programme.desc: Simple colored powder can break down the barriers between people. Since the dawn of antiquity, to mark the spring equinox, the whole of India celebrates Holi, the festival of colors. During this celebration, Indians of all castes throw colored powder in the faces of people they meet.

programme.title: Darwin Northern Territory
programme.desc: In Darwin, Jason swims in the Crocodile Tank and visits Litchfield National Park. He also goes heli-pubbing, savours the delicious barra burger, then catches, and cooks, black pepper mud crab. Delicious!

programme.title: Dining With Geishas
programme.desc: Rural Japan: Tony decides to look for a more relaxing, traditional Japanese culinary experience in the countryside. Tony travels to an old-style Japanese inn that specializes in kaiseki cuisine, ancient tea ceremony, and local ingredients.

programme.title: Malta
programme.desc: A delightful Mediterranean climate, fantastic beaches, and fascinating historic sites only begin to describe the Maltese experience. Few places in the world possess a more exquisite coastline. The HBO series, "Game of Thrones," filmed portions of the series in Malta's capital city of Valletta.

programme.title: Dublin
programme.desc: At the confluence of Muir Eireann and the Irish Sea on Ireland’s East Coast stands the capital city of Dublin. Join Laura McKenzie as she enjoys the perfect pint at Gravity Bar atop Guinness Brewery, explore Dublin Castle, and become acquainted with The Four Seasons Dublin.

programme.title: Paris
programme.desc: There is more than enough to keep you busy in Paris. Historic sites such as the Louvre, Notre Dame Cathedral, the Picasso Museum, and Paris Opera House only get you started. Tuileries Garden and Paris Beach offer a unique way to relax and have fun, and Sacre-Coeur offers a 360-degree view of city.

programme.title: Los Angeles
programme.desc: Rent a Rolls Royce and roll through L.A. in style. When you hit Hollywood and Vine you know you are in the city’s heart, as the Pantages Theater, Capitol Records Building, Grauman's Chinese Theatre, and Kodak Theater greet you. Get the skinny on everything Beverly Hills and visit Olvera Street.

programme.title: Prague
programme.desc: Explore the heart of Bohemia as we join Laura in Prague. Visit Prague Castle, the Charles Bridge, and the Jewish Quarter. Gothic Loket Castle is a short, scenic drive away from the city and worth the tour. Next up the must-see spa town of Karlovy Vary.

programme.title: Britain's Historic Countryside
programme.desc: First stops are Camden Market and Notting Hill Gate. Enjoy a treat as Laura escorts you to the birthplace of pomp and circumstance, Buckingham Palace. Then mosey down to Windsor Castle before taking on London with Big Ben and Tower Bridge.

programme.title: Italy: Part 1
programme.desc: Experience the arresting appeal and elegance of Italy in six select locations. Take an invigorating stroll along the Mediterranean coast in Castello Federiciano, marvel at Alberobello’s august trullo dry stone huts, and more.

programme.title: Shedd Aquarium: Wild Reef
programme.desc: Experience the wonder of the Shedd Aquarium’s wild reef as light dances off the colorful aquatic sea life that peacefully swim past in the crystal-clear water. Ambient sound makes you feel as if you are deep beneath the ocean.

programme.title: Delhi and Agra, India
programme.desc: From the serene beauty of one man's architectural love poem to a woman, the Taj Mahal, to the crowded alleys of downtown New Delhi, India is a feast for the senses. Maxa discovers temples straight out of Disneyland and consults a street astrologer who tells him he will live a long life.

programme.title: Rajasthan, India
programme.desc: Tour the royal rooms behind the sandstone walls of the Mehrangarh Fort, perched high above the city of Jodhpur. In the countryside outside of Jodhpur, villagers, who have never seen a Westerner, invite Rudy Maxa into their homes, and the maharajah of Jodhpur explains why his palace is now a hotel.

programme.title: Istanbul, Turkey
programme.desc: In Istanbul, evidence of historical invasion exists everywhere. From the Romans to the Ottomans, this tumultuous city has seen it all, and its architecture, cuisine, and customs reflect that reality. Tour the Grand Bazaar, Topkapi Palace, the Hagia Sophia, the Blue Mosque, and the Spice Market.

programme.title: Turkey's Turquoise Coast
programme.desc: Ancient towns of Ephesus, Antalya, Myra and Dalyan dot the Turkish coast, tempting visitors to step back in time when lavish Roman homes and markets dotted the landscape. Boarding a gulet, the traditional wooden Turkish boat, for a Blue Cruise, Rudy departs from the popular seaside town of Bodrum.

programme.title: Bangkok, Thailand
programme.desc: Rudy takes you off the beaten path into the quiet, residential klongs, or canals, of Bangkok. Marvel at the Emerald Buddha, visit the city's fresh markets, join locals offering incense and flowers at colorful outdoor shrines, celebrate the king's 80th birthday with an all-night party, and more.

programme.title: Thailand, The Golden Triangle
programme.desc: The saffron robes of Buddhist monks, the vivid colors of local blossoms, and the brilliant emerald of rice fields make the Golden Triangle a magical corner of the world. Join Rudy as he takes mahout lessons and gets soaked steering his elephant into the river that separates Thailand from Burma.

programme.title: Village of Swimming Cows
programme.desc: What happens when eco-minded, city-dwelling Berliners move in with Polish farmers in the country? Take a charming, extraordinarily funny look at how friendship and communication can overcome boundaries, and how nourishing the mind, body, and spirit begins with love and respect for Mother Earth.

programme.title: France's Via Aquitania
programme.desc: Follow the Via Aquitania, an ancient Roman road that connected a network of cities and was the main trade route between the Mediterranean Sea and the Atlantic Ocean. Traces of the region’s history abound and will become clearer to you the more you hear the people who love this land speak of it.

programme.title: The Road of the Nomadic Soul: from Kyrgyzstan to Tajikistan
programme.desc: Your journey begins with a trek from Bishkek, the capital of Kyrgyzstan, to Lake Issyk Kul. Then, head through the mountains and pasture where shepherds live. On your way to Tajikistan, you will cross the Trans-Alay mountains in the Western Pamirs populated by the Kyrgyz people of nomadic tradition.

programme.title: Philippines - The Unexplored Archipelago
programme.desc: The Philippines consist of roughly 7,000 islands, including the island of Palawan, one of the wildest islands in the world. Still very undeveloped and traditional in its ways, Palawan's jungles, mountains, abundant wildlife, and beaches make it one of the most biodiverse islands in the Philippines.

programme.title: Dining With Geishas
programme.desc: Rural Japan: Tony decides to look for a more relaxing, traditional Japanese culinary experience in the countryside. Tony travels to an old-style Japanese inn that specializes in kaiseki cuisine, ancient tea ceremony, and local ingredients.

programme.title: Cobra Heart-Food That Makes You Manly
programme.desc: Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam: After taking a cyclo-ride through Ho Chi Minh City and trying various foods from roadside vendors and markets, Tony tests his might with a few shots of snake wine and a live cobra heart.

programme.title: America's Musical Journey
programme.desc: A cross-country adventure through the musical heritage of America and the cultural cities where America's music was born.

programme.title: Photographing Monument Valley
programme.desc: Photographer Ian Ruhter captures visuals with a camera built from a truck.

programme.title: America. The Beautiful: Kayaking Columbia River Gorge
programme.desc: Kayaker Rush Sturges rides life-threatening rapids and waterfalls.

programme.title: Righteous Bites
programme.desc: In Los Angeles, the Fat Jerry sammie, in Monterey, California, abalone sliders, in Aiea, Hawaii, oxtail soups and grilled turkey sandwich.

programme.title: Grillin Chillin Huli Chicken

programme.title: Shaytana's Eye
programme.desc: The peaceful Kingdom of Kale is thrown into chaos after the Citadel is overthrown by the dark forces of Kreel and Xax. After his family farm is destroyed by the Xaxian army, young William Tell is visited by the mystical Kalem who reveals that he has been chosen to seek the legendary Crystal Arrow.

programme.title: On Our Own
programme.desc: Four newly orphaned siblings are out of options. With no blood relatives, they are about to be sent to separate foster homes. To keep from being split apart, they decide to bust out of the orphanage and take off in a beat-up VW in search of an estranged uncle, but detectives soon catch their tail.

programme.title: A Cat and Mouse Game
programme.desc: A family and their cat, Marcel, encounter a pet mouse (Cheeky) left behind by the former residents of a summer cottage. Like the classic comedy series, “Tom and Jerry”, Marcel watches and attempts to capture the mischievous Cheeky who constantly eludes him. What will become of the chase in time?

programme.title: The Duelists
programme.desc: 200 years ago, Tobias and Samuel died attempting to win the affections of Ariadne, who loved neither man. Now, both men are cursed to relive their terrible demise once a year on the anniversary of their deaths, but this year is different.

programme.title: Bertie
programme.desc: David Rhodes is a writer, and in anticipation of the sale of the screen rights to his latest novel, the Rhodes family purchases the Milton mansion. Siblings Kate and John fall in love with the home, even when they discover Bertie, a ghost.

programme.title: Maricela
programme.desc: Maricela and her mother Eugenia have fled El Salvador for America. When Eugenia becomes a live-in housekeeper to the affluent Gannett family, conflict arises when Maricela clashes with teenage Stacy Gannett. Can Maricela win Stacy's friendship while remaining true to her own ideals and values?

programme.title: Book 7: The River of Adventure (Part 1)
programme.desc: As the family prepares to disembark to Turkey, Sir George contacts Bill asking him to investigate and gather information on a smalltime blundering criminal named Uma. Once in Turkey, they meet a boy named Oola, a badly treated assistant of a snake charmer.

programme.title: My Classic Car
programme.desc: On this episode of My Classic Car, Dennis makes his way to Logan, UT for the Cache Valley Cruise-In.

programme.title: The Tomb of the Unknown Warrior
programme.desc: Will and the band are on a diplomatic mission to Mendica where two rival tribes, the Mendicans and the Sarks, have been fighting. Will is worried that the two tribes are too busy feuding to understand the threat of Xax's Warriors.

programme.title: The 1960s
programme.desc: The 1960s is a decade of both cultural and technological change. Home entertainment goes from the kitchen table to the TV screen when the video game console is unveiled, and the United States finally wins the decade-long space race, taking a giant step for mankind by landing astronauts on the moon.

programme.title: The Challenge
programme.desc: A statue of Xax with crystal eyes has been placed in every village as a form of surveillance for Kreel and Xax to spy over the kingdom. Lalia refuses to worship the idol and is taken prisoner. Will discovers the type of crystal that is being used to transmit the images, and its source.

programme.title: Lucy with George Burns
programme.desc: Upon visiting the bank Lucy works for, George Burns discovers Lucy’s instinctive style of comedic humor and asks her to become a partner in his show. Mr. Mooney, who believes this is the perfect opportunity to rid himself of Lucy at the bank, accepts the offer to become her talent agent.

programme.title: Lucy and the Submarine
programme.desc: Mr. Mooney forgets to sign some important papers prior to leaving the bank for Naval Reserve Training, so Lucy must travel to the submarine he is about to embark on. Dressing up as a sailor, Lucy boards the craft to look for Mooney, but before she can exit, the submarine sets sail.

programme.title: Lucy and Bean Queen
programme.desc: When Mr. Mooney refuses to co-sign Lucy's loan for new furniture, she launches an elaborate scheme to win the money from a company manufacturing beans.

programme.title: Lucy and the Ring-a-Ding Ring
programme.desc: When Lucy tries on an expensive ring Mr. Mooney just made for his wife, the ring gets stuck on Lucy’s finger, leaving Mr. Mooney in doubt as to whether he will be able to give his wife the special anniversary present he made for her.

programme.title: Lucy Flies to London
programme.desc: When Lucy enters a dog food jingle contest, she wins the grand prize: a trip to London, England. Lucy packs her ticket in her luggage, and misses her plane, only to find herself seated next to Mr. Mooney on the next flight to depart.

programme.title: Lucy Gets a Roommate
programme.desc: To cut down on expenses, Lucy advertises for a roommate, selecting a shy Librarian named Carol Bradford. To get Carol to come out of her shell, Lucy and Mary Jane throw a party and invite a group of musicians to perform.

programme.title: Lucy and Carol in Palm Springs
programme.desc: When Lucy calls in sick to work so that she may be a part of her roommate Carol’s musical act at a Palm Springs resort, Lucy’s boss Mr. Mooney, on vacation himself, is unfortunately staying at the very same hotel.

programme.title: Episode 7
programme.desc: Giles is arrested by policeman, Officer Costello, while crime-fighting hero, Silver Lining, is disappointed that he did not solve the crime after discovering that Octavia provided much needed clues. There is only one superhero in Sunset Cove, but is it Silver Lining or his arch enemy, Bad Mood?

programme.title: Cop Shot; Girls Survive Big Wave; Aussie Capsized; Deserted Baby Success; Dog Saves Boy
programme.desc: Don Mauldin had a premonition that something terrible was going to happen, and asked his wife Maggie to pray for him. Three young girls are drawn to the big surf conditions in California. A distress call off the east coast of Australia puts members of the Coast Guard on alert and in danger.

programme.title: Prayers for Theresa; Cop in a Wash; Valley Hills Vision; Jet Ski Rescue; Heaven's Window
programme.desc: Two-year-old Theresa and her family were in the process of moving into a new home when she was abducted and drowned by a teenage boy. The community rallies together. A photo taken on a field trip to Our Lady of Valley Hill in Kentucky, shows what appears to be a gateway to Heaven. And more!

programme.title: Invasion
programme.desc: The notorious Samuel Scaggs and his band of pirates land on the island and take over the Robinson tree house. As the family prepares to celebrate the Fourth of July, Scaggs demands that David Robinson renounce America, or be put to death.

programme.title: Charlie & Me
programme.desc: This is the touching story of an 11-year-old girl who has an extraordinarily close relationship with her grandfather and a complex relationship with her widowed father. While other children her age go out on the town, Casey goes out with her grandfather Charlie, and loves every minute of it.

programme.title: Lone Star Kid
programme.desc: After witnessing a severe accident, a compassionate 11-year-old boy named Brian Zimmerman believes that the town of Crabb, Texas needs a mayor, and Brian thinks he is "the man" for the job. This inspiring true story shows the potential for good that even a young boy can have on his community.

programme.title: Runaway Hearts
programme.desc: At a poignant moment in their lives, 11-year-old Tevin and his 5-year-old sister Angel escape their dysfunctional home to live in the streets. With nowhere to go, Tevin and Angel meet two people who need a miracle just as badly as they do.

programme.title: A Cat and Mouse Game

programme.title: Konrad
programme.desc: Konrad was created as a perfect “instant 8-year-old child” in a factory, but due to a glitch in the factory's computer, he is delivered to Bertie Bartolotti by mistake. When the factory realizes a mistake was made, and recalls Konrad, Konrad does not wish to leave his new family and friends.

programme.title: Gulliver's Travels
programme.desc: Giant Gulliver washes ashore on tiny Lilliput and attempts to prevent war between the small kingdom of Lilliput and its equally minuscule rival Blefuscu. In pursuit of his endeavor, can Gulliver smooth the way towards love between the Princess and Prince of the two opposing lands?

programme.desc: Moises, a talented young filmmaker, discovers that his true destiny is to save the town that he desires so much to escape. The question Moises longs to receive clarity on is- Do we choose our dreams, or do our dreams choose us?
