programme.title: Breakdown
programme.desc: With Oregon in their sights, Dylan openly challenges Brock’s decision to escape Chicago for a simpler life in Oregon. Just when smoother roads appear to be prevailing, something profoundly mysterious occurs that changes the Turner's plans.

programme.title: Breakthrough
programme.desc: When things appear to be going from bad to worse, God’s miraculous energy inspires Dylan to contemplate his depth of faith. The question is, will Brock and Dylan together discover the power that God’s love has to cast away all fear?

programme.title: Episode 13
programme.desc: Giles joins forces with the manipulative Sabrina in his attempts to end Octavia and Josh’s relationship. Commander Vermont attempts to put strategies in place, unaware that Mr. Dorsey is pleading with the alien generals for another opportunity to find the lost city of Atlantis.

programme.title: Fireman Rescues Girl; Flight 811; Quarterback; The Other Boy; Acting Upon Fate
programme.desc: When an explosion blows a hole in the fuselage of Flight 811, the passengers panic, but the captain and his crew are determined to save them. A 12-year-old boy is hit by a car, but when a witness recalls the incident, they recall his guardian angel stepping in front of him and taking the hit.

programme.title: Electric Fence; Mother and Child Reunion; Dog Saves Master; Life on a Line
programme.desc: A mother and her baby were miraculously saved after being thrown overboard in a raging storm, a mysterious force stops a man from touching a metal fence that had a hidden broken power line touching it, and a dog and his owner share a special connection as the dog saves the man's life. And more!

programme.title: Stoked on Fishing - An Unforgettable Trip, South Lake, Part Two
programme.desc: This show was filmed in late October of 2019. Four months prior, in June of 2019, Tim Carnahan was diagnosed with Glioblastoma, Brain Cancer. According to Tim's medical team, his life expectancy could be between three months and 18 months. Fast forward to now, 2020; today's update is one we hoped would never come. With a heavy heart and tear-filled eyes, we share with you that Tim Carnahan has passed away after battling for close to 12 months. It only fits that the last words to pass his lips were I love you, Lory, and keep fishing. While his time on earth was cut short, the amount of joy he experienced and shared with others was genuinely tremendous and will never be forgotten. If you would like to help out in any way, lory and friends have put together a Go Fund Me page to ease the financial burden of medical bills and afford lory some time to greave and transition into life without Tim. We love you, Tim. Rest in peace, buddy.

programme.title: Alien Creatures from Beyond: Monsters, Ghosts and Vampires
programme.desc: Are there creatures still unknown to science lurking in the remote areas of our planet? Hundreds of eyewitnesses say unquestionably YES. Lurking in Magog is the elusive Memphre, a thirty-foot lake monster that stalks the peaceful waters of Lake Memphremagog. Wilno, Ontario is a small town steeped in its heritage, locals believe that when a person takes their own life, then is buried on sacred ground, that person will become a vampire who will walk the streets, preying on their family members. The Bytown Museum sits at the gateway to the Rideau Canal and may also be a gateway to the paranormal. Bell Island is a place steeped in mysteries and legends encountered firsthand by local residents living around the marshes known as Dobbin’s Garden. The residents have named their local Banshee “The Bell Island Hag” explaining that sometimes she appears as a beautiful woman in white, but more often as a horrifying deformed old hag. Men have been known to enter the marshes and then emerge days later scared to death with no memory of what happened, or where they had been. Banshees, Lake Monsters, Vampires and more will be encountered in this special compilation of “Alien Creatures from Beyond.”

programme.title: The Wildman of Kentucky, The Mystery of Panther Rock
programme.desc: There is probably no other unknown creature that arouses more curiosity than the Bigfoot or Sasquatch. Yes, there is the Loch Ness Monster, the Chupacabra and other great beasts of Lore but the Bigfoot remains the most compelling as it pulls us towards ourselves…shadowing the unknown X factor of our very origins. The case files contain thousands of reported sightings, yet no actual specimen has ever been found. Hundreds of photographs exist, but the creature has not been identified. Still, the clues accumulate year after year. In the words of one Bigfoot investigator, “It is an extremely complex phenomenon with no starting point and few geographical limits.” If this creature does exist then it most certainly must be a relative of man. Species? Unknown at this time. In the heart of Kentucky there is an ancient and sacred ground known as Panther Rock. For many years tales of strange events have been reported but never investigated in full. Now, for the first time an intrepid group of explorers ventures into the unknown to discover the truth. Join the Reality Team of Special Investigators as they uncover new Bigfoot witnesses and historical tales. Journey with them into the dark woods of the Frazier Land and witness amazing paranormal and often terrifying events.

programme.title: Ontario Experience - Crane's Lochaven Wilderness Lodge
programme.desc: Troy Lindner boats into Crane's Lochaven Wilderness Resort on Northeastern Ontario's French River, an outstanding multi-species fishery steeped in history.

programme.desc: Traveling across the country to Captiva Island, Florida, our other favorite coast to kayak fish. Hundreds of large permit school up on an offshore reef where two of our lucky Hobie kayak anglers find themselves right in the middle of it.

programme.title: Hobie Fishing - Kayak Fishing for Albies on Cape Cod
programme.desc: Got Albies? A kayak is perfect for chasing these line screaming speed machines around as they boil up on schools of micro bait. Can you think of a more stealthy wait to target these finicky fish? On the tail end of this show we catch up with fly fishing legend, Lefty Kreh, and talk about the good ol’ days on back bay circa 1950 catching largemouth bass, and then we test it out ourselves from our Hobies.

programme.title: Hobie Fishing - Kayak Fishing Heaven in Florida's Fellsmere
programme.desc: Big bass, alligators and incredible bird life are all part of the amazing ecosystem that make up Fellsmere Reservoir. Watch as our anglers take their Hobie fishing kayaks across the country one more time to the ultimate kayak fishing heaven in Florida.

programme.title: Alien Creatures from Beyond: Monsters, Ghosts and Vampires
programme.desc: Are there creatures still unknown to science lurking in the remote areas of our planet? Hundreds of eyewitnesses say unquestionably YES. Lurking in Magog is the elusive Memphre, a thirty-foot lake monster that stalks the peaceful waters of Lake Memphremagog. Wilno, Ontario is a small town steeped in its heritage, locals believe that when a person takes their own life, then is buried on sacred ground, that person will become a vampire who will walk the streets, preying on their family members. The Bytown Museum sits at the gateway to the Rideau Canal and may also be a gateway to the paranormal. Bell Island is a place steeped in mysteries and legends encountered firsthand by local residents living around the marshes known as Dobbin’s Garden. The residents have named their local Banshee “The Bell Island Hag” explaining that sometimes she appears as a beautiful woman in white, but more often as a horrifying deformed old hag. Men have been known to enter the marshes and then emerge days later scared to death with no memory of what happened, or where they had been. Banshees, Lake Monsters, Vampires and more will be encountered in this special compilation of “Alien Creatures from Beyond.”

programme.title: The Wildman of Kentucky, The Mystery of Panther Rock
programme.desc: There is probably no other unknown creature that arouses more curiosity than the Bigfoot or Sasquatch. Yes, there is the Loch Ness Monster, the Chupacabra and other great beasts of Lore but the Bigfoot remains the most compelling as it pulls us towards ourselves…shadowing the unknown X factor of our very origins. The case files contain thousands of reported sightings, yet no actual specimen has ever been found. Hundreds of photographs exist, but the creature has not been identified. Still, the clues accumulate year after year. In the words of one Bigfoot investigator, “It is an extremely complex phenomenon with no starting point and few geographical limits.” If this creature does exist then it most certainly must be a relative of man. Species? Unknown at this time. In the heart of Kentucky there is an ancient and sacred ground known as Panther Rock. For many years tales of strange events have been reported but never investigated in full. Now, for the first time an intrepid group of explorers ventures into the unknown to discover the truth. Join the Reality Team of Special Investigators as they uncover new Bigfoot witnesses and historical tales. Journey with them into the dark woods of the Frazier Land and witness amazing paranormal and often terrifying events.

programme.title: Stoked on Fishing - An Unforgettable Trip, South Lake, Part Two
programme.desc: This show was filmed in late October of 2019. Four months prior, in June of 2019, Tim Carnahan was diagnosed with Glioblastoma, Brain Cancer. According to Tim's medical team, his life expectancy could be between three months and 18 months. Fast forward to now, 2020; today's update is one we hoped would never come. With a heavy heart and tear-filled eyes, we share with you that Tim Carnahan has passed away after battling for close to 12 months. It only fits that the last words to pass his lips were I love you, Lory, and keep fishing. While his time on earth was cut short, the amount of joy he experienced and shared with others was genuinely tremendous and will never be forgotten. If you would like to help out in any way, lory and friends have put together a Go Fund Me page to ease the financial burden of medical bills and afford lory some time to greave and transition into life without Tim. We love you, Tim. Rest in peace, buddy.

programme.title: Canoo Revealed
programme.desc: We are here to change the way the world thinks about transportation. Rather than designing our vehicles the traditional way, we design our vehicles from the inside out, crafting every feature with a focus on what matters most to our users to give them the best possible experience. We engineered our electric platform with this in mind, to enable unprecedented creative freedom and adaptability. - Continuing our pursuit of bringing clean energy vehicles to everyone, our next adventure is electrifying business fleets with a series of vehicles thoughtfully designed with the end user in mind, bringing more productivity to more people.

programme.title: Kia e-Niro Virtual Testdrive
programme.desc: Visualize your next EV by taking a virtual testdrive. Explore the benefits of electric vehicles in a fun and informative way, harnessing the latest experiential technologies to highlight the many ways in which EVs are superior to ICE vehicles.

programme.title: Bolt EV Academy

programme.title: Airspeeder - Our Flying Car Future
programme.desc: “Nothing drives innovation like racing. The world is ready for advanced air mobility and we are proud to make history by introducing the world’s first racing series for flying electric cars. Airspeeder and EXA represent the future of motorsport and a compelling and exhilarating showcase of the potential of electric flying cars as this generation’s defining mobility revolution.” - Matthew Pearson, Founder, Airspeeder and Alauda Aeronautics - EXA is Airspeeder’s first electric flying racing series. Up to four teams with two remote pilots per team will compete in three individual events across the globe through 2021. They will race ‘blade-to-blade’ over locations inaccessible to traditional motorsport.

programme.desc: Chelsea Sexton, Paul Scott, Forth Mobility, and several owners come together to discuss how electric cars have evolved and where we currently are in the state of this developing technology. It covers issues and experiences related to charging, battery degradation, and range anxiety, along with detailed explanations of charging levels, types of electric vehicles, and the future of hydrogen. - This film prepares viewers with the knowledge needed for properly assessing vehicle options, along with considerations for charging, and knowledge about what they may need to know before making a purchase.

programme.title: Who Stole the Electric Car?
programme.desc: In the year 1995, a self-centered average guy steals a prototype electric car in a crazy attempt to win back his Africa-bound environmentalist girlfriend. During his road trip from the Motor City to Southern California, he teams up with a vegetarian sidekick and, pursued by the police, the duo race across the country. . . without using a single drop of gasoline. - Directors: James Dastoli, Robert Dastoli - Starring: Carl Fieler, Chris Shields

programme.title: Astypalea: Smart, Sustainable Island
programme.desc: Astypalea up until now is probably only known to insiders. The small island is located in the Aegean Sea, it belongs to Greece and is especially known for its butterflies. This is likely to change in the future: Astypalea will become a model for smart, emission-free mobility. The island wants to prove that a purely electric transport system is already possible today – without any restrictions on the mobility of its inhabitants. We explain the details.

programme.title: Audi Annual Press Conference 2020
programme.desc: 2020 was dominated by a global pandemic and great upheaval, which therefore shifted the focus even more strongly to the question of responsible actions. As part of the automotive industry, we are responsible for our employees and customers, for stable economic growth, and for a sustainable business model. Despite – or precisely because of – the current challenges, we are in a position where we can make a big difference. At Audi, we see ambitious climate targets, the paradigm shift toward software, and the impetus created by new competitors as an opportunity to play an active part in shaping the future of mobility. Our Board of Management team, which has been active in a new constellation for about a year, will provide an overview on how Audi handled the unusual year of 2020 and on which future topics we have our sights firmly set.

programme.title: Lords of the Mafia
programme.desc: Japanese Yakuza- - Organized crime syndicates from Japan are now a major menace all over the Pacific Rim. Also known as the “boryokudan,” which means “the violent ones,” they are feared for their ruthlessness and strict codes of violence. Their “Little Caesar” is the flamboyant Yoshinori Watanabe, who was inducted in 1989 as “kumicho” (boss of bosses), presiding over the 105 “oyabun” (bosses) of Japan’s 750 Yakuza gangs. With 22,000 soldiers, Watanabe’s outfit — the Yamaguchi-gumi — is easily the largest and most powerful.

programme.desc: Rusty Tidenberg, drag-racing aficionado, shocked friends and family by coming out as trans. Followed for 8 years by filmmaker Harrod Blank (son of Les Blank), Rusty guides us through the aftermath of her transition. Interwoven with lively tales of gender non-conforming individuals on the art-car circuit, Blank’s film is a sensitive and unpredictable love letter to people who fight to be unapologetically themselves.

programme.title: The Most Dangerous Year
programme.desc: As a dark wave of anti-transgender “bathroom bills” began sweeping across the nation, The Human Rights Campaign called 2016 the most dangerous year ever for transgender Americans. Filmmaker Vlada Knowlton captured the ensuing civil rights battle from the perspective of a group of embattled parents – including herself and her husband, parents of a young trans girl -- fighting to protect their children from discriminatory laws in their home state. While Knowlton passionately follows the story of anti-transgender legislation, the heart of the film lies in the stories of the families who accept and support their kids for exactly who they are.

programme.title: Political Animals
programme.desc: Political Animals celebrates the legendary civil rights victories of four trailblazing California state politicians: Carole Migden, Sheila Keuhl, Jackie Goldberg, and Christine Kehoe. Fierce and unrelenting, these courageous women toppled a partisan majority and emerged victors to pass historic legislation for social justice and LGBT+ equality. It was a hard fight – filled with vehemently heated debates and hateful insults hurled by opponents. Today, the message behind Political Animals is more important than ever as the current political theatre unfurls around the globe. These inspiring biographies further reveal the critical importance for public resistance at the local level to pressure lawmakers to enact difficult change. Political Animals is a clear call to action for a new era of greater democratic participation. We invite you to follow in the footsteps of these historic leaders and become the next pioneering political animal!

programme.title: Kumu Hina
programme.desc: Imagine a world where a little boy can grow up to be the woman of his dreams, and a young girl can rise to become a leader among men. Welcome to Kumu Hina's Hawai'i. Kumu Hina tells the inspiring story of Hina Wong-Kalu, a transgender native Hawaiian teacher, or kumu, who brings to life Hawai‘i's traditional embrace of mahu - those who embody both male and female spirit. Produced by Emmy-winning directors Dean Hamer and Joe Wilson in association with ITVS and Pacifc Islanders in Communications, the film traces Hina's evolution from Collin Wong, a timid high school boy, to her present position as a married woman and cultural director of a school in one of Honolulu's grittier neighborhoods. When Ho‘onani, a charismatic 6th grade girl, asks to join the school's all-male hula troupe, Kumu Hina gives her the opportunity to express her inner male spirit. As teacher and student prepare for a climactic end-of-year public performance, they meet many obstacles, but hold fast to the idea that being true to oneself matters most.

programme.title: The Library
programme.desc: As we seek to honor and celebrate the countless LGBTQ individuals, communities, sub-communities, and dynasties that have flourished in the face of adversity over decades, it dawned on us that there are so many unknown and untold stories about gay history, vocabulary, vernacular, and the human experiences that fuel the formation of cultures and identities based on authentic self-expression and love. As we discovered these stories, we wished for a gay “library” where anyone could visit and learn, in bite-size portions, about crucial events in gay history, gay heroes and icons past and present, fascinating sub-cultures, slang terms, scientific references, political movements... Essentially, a record of all the bits of queer education that are at risk of being lost or misinterpreted — information that we all crave as members of LGBTQ communities and as Allies. Do you know the story of the first Pride parade? Ever wondered what “Skoliosexual,” “Polycule,” or “Doppelbanger” means? The Library is open — and ready to clue you in.

programme.title: Verbier Festival: Boris Berezovsky
programme.desc: Boris Berezovsky è considerato uno dei migliori rappresentanti della scuola pianistica russa, soprattutto per la sua potente tecnica. Per il 15° anniversario del Verbier Festival, in programma un recital con la Sonata in si minore di Franz Liszt, seguito da brani di Schumann. Un vero e proprio viaggio nel romanticismo.

programme.title: Vox Luminis: Handel in Versailles
programme.desc: È nella sontuosa Cappella Reale di Versailles che il gruppo Vox Luminis porta Georg Friedrich Handel sotto i riflettori. Specializzato nel repertorio barocco inglese, italiano e tedesco, il gruppo Vox Luminis, sotto la direzione di Lionel Meunier, esegue con leggerezza e raffinatezza due salmi, un'opera lirica e un oratorio.

programme.title: Mozart Requiem - Claudio Abbado
programme.desc: Sotto la direzione di Claudio Abbado, la Lucerne Festival Orchestra, accompagnata dal Coro della Radio Bavarese e dal Coro della Radio Svedese, ha eseguito con grazia il Requiem di W. A. Mozart al Festival di Lucerna nell'estate 2012. Le voci solenni di Anna Prohaska (soprano), Sara Mingardo (contralto), Maximilian Schmitt (tenore) e René Pape (basso) esprimono la bellezza e la profondità di questo capolavoro.

programme.title: Leonidas Kavakos And Yuja Wang
programme.desc: Due degli artisti più emblematici del Festival di Verbier interpretano insieme le opere di Brahms in un ricco concerto di musica da camera. Acclamato all'unanimità dal mondo della musica classica dal 1985, quando fece scalpore diventando il più giovane vincitore del prestigioso Concorso Sibelius, il violinista greco Leonidas Kavakos combina in questo concerto il suo virtuosismo con quello della pianista Yuja Wang, un'artista affermata a soli 26 anni.

programme.title: Paolo Arrivabeni - ORW
programme.desc: L'opera è sinonimo di cantanti. Eppure l'orchestra sinfonica gioca un ruolo cruciale in queste opere musicali e teatrali. L'Orchestre Royal de Wallonie - Liège, sotto la direzione di Paolo Arrivabeni, ci introduce quindi alla ricchezza della musica strumentale di alcune opere.

programme.title: B. Philharmoniker: Gershwin Night
programme.desc: Il Waldbühne di Berlino, residenza estiva dell'orchestra filarmonica della città, i Berliner Philharmoniker, è uno degli anfiteatri all'aperto più belli d'Europa. Nell'estate del 2003, il direttore d'orchestra giapponese Seji Ozawa ha diretto la famosa orchestra su successi di Gershwin come Un américain à Paris, Rhapsody in Blue, I Got Rhythm ... Ospite speciale: Il famoso trio jazz di Marcus Roberts.

programme.title: Daniel Oren & Saioa Hernandez - ORW
programme.desc: L'affascinante soprano spagnolo Saioa Hernández, con la sua voce potente e ammaliante, interpreta le famose arie d'opera italiane in concerto. Questo spettacolo ci permette di apprezzare il bel canto "l'arte del canto lirico" utilizzato nelle opere dal XVII secolo. Valorizzando le capacità tecniche dei cantanti, a volte a scapito dell'espressione scenica, la voce vola come fosse un uccellino.

programme.desc: Girato al Teatro Mariinsky, questo spettacolo vede la partecipazione di alcuni dei più famosi ballerini del teatro di San Pietroburgo, tra cui Ulyana Lopatkina, Igor Zelensky e Andrian Fadeyev, accanto al direttore d'orchestra Tugan Sokhiev. I Gioielli di George Balanchine sono parte integrante del repertorio della compagnia - uno dei più grandi al mondo, sia per numero che per fama.

programme.title: Symphonic Dances: Zahia Ziouani
programme.desc: A capo dell' Orchestra Sinfonica Divertimento (fondata nel 1998, in residenza a Stains dal 2005), Zahia Ziouani è riuscita a diversificare il pubblico della musica classica. Gli studenti dei conservatori della regione dell'Île-de-France si uniscono a lei per un viaggio nel repertorio sinfonico sotto il segno della danza, dalla tarantella italiana alla farandola provenzale, passando per il gopak ucraino.

programme.title: Berliner Philharmoniker: Abbado
programme.desc: Nel 2001, the Berlin Philharmonic Orchestra diretta dall’italiano Claudio Abbado suona tutte le sinfonie di Beethoven sul palco dell’Accademia Nazionale di Santa Cecilia a Roma. La Sinfonia n. 2 in RE maggiore fu scritta da Beethoven proprio quando fu diagnosticata la sua sordita’ ma la stessa composizione non ne risente in alcun modo e conferma a pieno titolo il ritmo e la dinamica musicale come elementi distintivi del compositore.

programme.title: Giuseppe Verdi: La Traviata - ORW
programme.desc: La Traviata, "La Devota", un'opera in tre atti, con un libretto di Francesco Maria Piave basato sul romanzo e la commedia La Dame aux Camélias di Alexandre Dumas fils, è una delle opere più popolari. Rappresenta la redenzione attraverso l'amore per mezzo del personaggio di Violetta. Questo ruolo, notevolmente interpretato da Patrizia Ciofi che unisce forza e fragilità, richiede assoluto virtuosismo.

programme.title: Berliner Philharmoniker - S. Rattle
programme.desc: L'illustre Orchestra Filarmonica di Berlino, la Berliner Philharmoniker, ha fatto dell'Europakonzert una tradizione. Ogni anno i suoi musicisti celebrano la fondazione della loro orchestra in una città europea diversa. Nel 2008 si sono esibiti sotto alla direzione del grande direttore d'orchestra Sir Simon Rattle al Conservatorio Tchaikovsky di Mosca. In programma: Il Concerto per violino n. 1 in SOL minore di Max Bruch, la Sinfonia n. 7 di Beethoven e la Sinfonia di Igor Stravinsky in tre movimenti.

programme.title: The Four Seasons Of Buenos Aires
programme.desc: Il Trio Zadig rivisita la famosa opera di Piazzolla: Le quattro stagioni di Buenos Aires e le conferisce freschezza e audacia.

programme.title: Léo Delibes: Coppélia
programme.desc: Il coreografo e direttore artistico Eduardo Lao si è assunto il compito di reinventare Coppelia, utilizzando la sua versatile compagnia di 23 danzatori per contribuire con la sua personale visione. Egli sottolinea lo spirito comico di Coppelia mantenendo la partitura originale scritta da Léo Delibes nel 1870.

programme.title: Denis Matsuev at Concertgebouw
programme.desc: Il pianista russo Denis Matsuev, uno dei più grandi virtuosi del suo strumento, si esibisce qui in un recital solista sul palcoscenico del Concertgebouw di Amsterdam. In programma ci sono le Stagioni di Tchaikovsky, un classico della musica russa per celebrare il 175° compleanno del compositore nel 2015, e un'altra opera romantica: La Kreisleriana di Schumann. Egli esegue anche l'impressionante e virtuosistico "Tre Movimenti di Petrushka" di Stravinsky.

Ascoltate questa sinfonia drammatica e commovente eseguita dalla Israel Philharmonic Orchestra sotto la raffinata direzione di Vasily Petrenko.

La Sonata per pianoforte n. 59 di Haydn, la Sonata per pianoforte n. 32 di Beethoven e la "Melodia" di Christoph Willibald Gluck da Orfeo ed Euridice offrono a Kissin l'opportunità di mostrare la portata del suo virtuosismo e il lirismo delle sue interpretazioni, ma anche il suo carisma fenomenale.
